haReport:
This mission was flown by:
Ltn Patrik Schorner, Ltn Patrik Schorner
Uffz Heiner Waldbrunn, Uffz Heiner Waldbrunn

 The mission was flown from Bellevue Ferme aerodrome.

Successes include the following: 
On 09/02/1916 near Gironville.
A F.E.2b of Esc 2 was brought down by Baldemar May of FA 293b.
Cpl Theophile Villard was killed in action.
S/Lt Adolphe Lafaysse was killed in action.
Baldemar May was  flying a DFW C.V.

On 09/02/1916 near Ressons.
A F.E.2b of Esc 58 was brought down by Veit Eisenstein of FA 293b.
S/Lt Marceau Lacan was killed in action.
S/Lt Florent Terrade was killed in action.
Veit Eisenstein was  flying a DFW C.V.
